cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DC

This paper discusses energy efficiency in Software Defined Networking (SDN), which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses optimization models and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses security issues, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses hardware-based solutions, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
